For more on this, eNCA's Ronald Masinda is outside the school. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has condemned the violence at the Brackenfell High School in Cape Town. Ramaphosa says the allegations of racism at the school, should be investigated. READ: EFF, parents vow to return to Brackenfell High School Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) members protested against alleged racism at the school. Clashes ensued when parents confronted the protesters. Police made one arrest, and both parties are vowing to return to the school. READ: One suspect arrested at Brackenfell High School protest The President is urging all parties to exercise restraint. Ramaphosa says differences can be resolved through discussions.